印度[[昌迪加尔|昌迪加尔]]的'''议会大厦'''（Palace of Assembly）是由现代主义建筑师[[勒·柯布西耶|勒·柯布西耶]]设计<ref name="gua">{{cite news |first=Jason |last=Burke |url=https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2011/mar/07/chandigarh-le-corbusier-heritage-site |title=Le Corbusier's Indian masterpiece Chandigarh is stripped for parts | Art and design |work=The Guardian |date=7 March 2011 |accessdate=2013-07-02 |archive-date=2017-11-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107015622/https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2011/mar/07/chandigarh-le-corbusier-heritage-site |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/Conserving-Le-Corbusiers-heritage-comes-into-focus/articleshow/576101.cms? |title=Conserving Le Corbusier's heritage comes into focus |work=The Times Of India |date=23 March 2004 |accessdate=2014-09-16 |archive-date=2018-09-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180905114329/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/Conserving-Le-Corbusiers-heritage-comes-into-focus/articleshow/576101.cms |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

==历史==
建于1951-1962年。其所在的[[昌迪加尔政治中心建筑群|昌迪加尔政治中心建筑群]], 共包括议会大厦（Palace of Assembly）、[[秘书处大楼_(昌迪加尔)|秘书处大楼]]（Secretariat Building）、高等法院（High Court）<ref>{{cite news |first=Khushboo |last=Sandhu |url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/capitol-complex-as-le-corbusier-wanted-it/635844/ |title=Capitol Complex, as Le Corbusier wanted it, remains incomplete |work=Indian Express |date=19 June 2010 |accessdate=2013-07-02 |archive-date=2013-11-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131127074822/http://www.indianexpress.com/news/capitol-complex-as-le-corbusier-wanted-it/635844 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2016年7月17日，该建筑被列为[[世界遗产|世界遗产]]。<ref name="UNESCO1">{{Cite web |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/buddha-bihar-nalanda-mahavihara-unesco-world-heritage-site-chandigarh/1/717209.html |title=Tile: UNESCO approves all 3 Indian nominations for heritage tag, Publisher: India Today news, Published on: 18 July 2016, Accessed on: 18 July 2016 |access-date=2020-11-15 |archive-date=2016-07-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160719134259/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/buddha-bihar-nalanda-mahavihara-unesco-world-heritage-site-chandigarh/1/717209.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | date=15 July 2016 | agency=UNESCO World Heritage Centre | accessdate=15 July 2016 | language=en | url=https://whc.unesco.org/en/news/1524 | title=Four sites inscribed on UNESCO’s World Heritage List | work=whc.unesco.org | archive-date=2016-07-16 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160716131638/https://whc.unesco.org/en/news/1524 | dead-url=no }}</ref>

